## 8. Signal Capture (Self-Improvement Loop)

Behavior contract lives in `.sumela/sumela-prompt.md` (`<signal_capture>`) and `self-improvement-curator/SKILL.md`. Schema lives in `wiki/_SCHEMA.md` Section 15.

Review command: `/evolve`.

**Governance mode:** `{{governance_mode}}`

- `solo` — `/evolve` applies approved changes directly to the working tree (the default; one developer owns the agent config).
- `team` — `/evolve` routes changes to the **agent-control surface** (`.sumela/rules/`, `.sumela/skills/`, `.sumela/sumela-prompt.md`, `wiki/_SCHEMA.md`, the registries, `.sumela/git-hooks/`) through a **pull request** so a code owner reviews them before they become everyone's standard. Lower-stakes `wiki`/`active-context` changes still apply directly. See `self-improvement-curator/SKILL.md` `<evolve_review_workflow>` and `.github/CODEOWNERS`.

