## 11. Memory Architecture — Graphify + Qdrant + Obsidian

Active four-tier search stack. Routing rules live in `using-second-brain` skill; this section is the index of moving parts.

| Tier | System | What it indexes | Trigger |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Qdrant `chat_history` collection | Session summaries (semantic chunks via Ollama `qwen3-embedding:0.6b`) | Past conversations, "geçen hafta ne konuştuk", prior decisions |
| 2 | Graphify graph (`graphify-out/graph.json`, `calls` edges) — agent reads via `scripts/query-graph.py` (primary) or `graphify` CLI (secondary for cluster/path) | Code AST + call graph + communities | Function/class lookups, callers/callees, impact analysis |
| 3 | Obsidian wiki (`_SEARCH_INDEX.md` + pages) | Curated knowledge — ADRs, sprint plans, entity definitions | Architectural rationale, sprint state, domain entities |
| 4 | Grep / Read fallback | Exact string match | When Tiers 1–3 return no hits |

Maintenance scripts (auto-invoked by `finishing-a-development-branch` and `context-handoff`):
- `scripts/auto-update-memory.py` — rebuilds Graphify graph + syncs to Obsidian + Qdrant health check.
- `scripts/session-ingest.py <summary.md>` — chunks + embeds + upserts session summary to Qdrant.
- `scripts/query-qdrant.py "<query>"` — Tier-1 semantic search CLI.

Prerequisites: Ollama (with `qwen3-embedding:0.6b`), Qdrant on `localhost:6333`, `graphify` CLI on PATH. If any is unavailable, lower tiers degrade gracefully (Qdrant down → markdown summary fallback; Graphify down → grep fallback).

